From: Michael Froman <mfroman@mozilla.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 2026 18:30:20 -0500
Subject: (tmp-cherry-pick) Revert "Integrate logging of RTX original sequence
 number in `Call`." (732ec1632f)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

This reverts commit 35236fc68a45fdc969fc63522137aff8bab307ea.

Reason for revert: We found two bugs in the original CL. `configuration` is read after being std::moved, and logging happened for all payload types (not just RTX ones). Reverting while we fix these bugs.

Original change's description:
> Integrate logging of RTX original sequence number in `Call`.
>
> With this change, we retain centralized logging of incoming packets, at
> the cost of having to do RTX decapsulation centrally as well. This was
> deemed better than pushing down the logging to the streams (where
> decapsulation fits better), due to lower risk for missing to log packets
> after future refactorings.
>
> Bug: b/305890678, b/423646186
